Use the standard library
This is how to prime_length of string:
   Remember that n is string's length
   When n is less than 2, then:
      The answer is 0
   End when
   Remember that i is 2
   Do this n times:
      When i is at most n, then:
         Leave the loop
      End when
      When remainder of n and i is 0, then:
         The answer is 0
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is 1
Now you know

>>> prime_length of [72, 101, 108, 108, 111]
1
>>> prime_length of [97, 98, 99, 100, 99, 98, 97]
1
>>> prime_length of [107, 105, 116, 116, 101, 110, 115]
1